                        PETER DEVITT
                   (Police-sergeant, N 32). I produce a certificate—(Read: "Hereford, March, 1854; 
John Smith convicted of breaking and entering a church, and stealing table-covers and other articles. Five Years' Penal Servitude")—the prisoner is the man, I had him in custody—his time would be up in March last.
